b863b240-787b-4fbd-bf04-04ab66efad8b	800d3a91-7011-449e-8089-d5b05e13d0d2	1	- **Qubits**: Probabilistic, represented by a vector in a 2‑dimensional Hilbert space.  \n  - *Example*:  \n    ```math\n    |ψ⟩ = α|0⟩ + β|1⟩,\n    ```\n    where `α, β ∈ ℂ` and `|α|² + |β|² = 1`.\n\nThe ability of a qubit to occupy a superposition of both 0 and 1 simultaneously is the root of quantum speed‑up in algorithms such as Shor’s and Grover’s.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Decoherence – The Big Challenge\n\n- **Mechanism**: Interaction with external degrees of freedom (thermal phonons, electromagnetic noise, etc.) entangles the qubit with its environment.\n- **Result**: Off‑diagonal terms in the density matrix decay, reducing the quantum state to a classical mixture.\n- **Mitigation Strategies**:\n  - **Isolation**: Cryogenic environments, vacuum chambers.\n  - **Error correction**: Quantum error‑correcting codes (e.g., surface codes).\n  - **Dynamical decoupling**: Applying pulse sequences to refocus coherence.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Related Topics (Contextual Links)\n\n	[0.044739075,0.040480863,-0.15973586,-0.047977734,0.07736224,0.01812203,0.04912379,0.007591296,-0.04965063,0.029478267,-0.014095379,0.043197863,0.031136807,0.035216108,-0.024546443,-0.018911753,0.032744695,0.017393172,0.03401261,-0.016403537,-0.036188688,-0.009713833,-0.022021322,-0.03356205,0.03925725,0.053482525,0.0055862437,-0.04717509,-0.01367035,-0.044423956,0.03936416,-0.040717293,-0.0092894435,-0.055053208,-0.06225331,-0.077342935,0.04782328,0.010784621,0.005206792,-0.00962483,0.008091138,-0.0674761,0.0037289287,-0.04730956,0.046792645,0.021858037,0.0440443,-0.0068763755,0.016279096,-0.039485056,0.039777406,0.022247145,0.07544249,0.012972914,0.0809284,0.051644713,-0.027297292,-0.02190941,0.058463853,0.022416057,-0.009657611,-0.034293786,0.0006975349,0.028537128,0.06517398,0.020768087,-0.009221908,0.049956173,-0.013813245,-0.033304334,0.06277519,-0.032504726,-0.017782165,0.04160287,0.02475095,0.02522506,0.00036093048,-0.03857645