a4ad0b63-2848-4197-a008-3183e228c317	800d3a91-7011-449e-8089-d5b05e13d0d2	2	- **Entanglement**: Correlations between qubits that exceed classical limits; essential for many quantum protocols.\n- **Quantum Gates**: Unitary operations (`X`, `H`, `CNOT`) that manipulate superposition and entanglement.\n- **Measurement**: Projective process collapsing the qubit into either `|0⟩` or `|1⟩`, yielding classical information.\n- **Physical Realizations**: Superconducting circuits, trapped ions, spin qubits, photonic qubits—each with distinct coherence times.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Broader Perspective\n\nQuantum computing is a rapidly evolving field where theory and experiment intersect. Understanding superposition and decoherence is foundational for exploring advanced concepts such as fault‑tolerant architectures, quantum simulation, and the eventual practical deployment of quantum advantage in cryptography, materials science, and optimization.\n\n---\n\n	[0.028586138,0.10532603,-0.16692331,-0.06775119,0.07792431,-0.022322536,0.046652704,-0.006571181,0.0053543923,0.0032450042,-0.040568307,0.02023956,0.019648911,-0.0059618987,0.0030116385,-0.01758358,0.007658323,-0.004756746,0.04792014,0.02008849,-0.03241752,-0.031063844,-0.0004321222,0.0017263606,0.009238544,0.053931452,-0.010977397,-0.043475304,-0.014576596,-0.018179484,0.041923195,-0.0917553,0.0107631935,-0.023367833,-0.03569627,-0.08691009,0.03084432,0.0075354395,0.035150487,-0.020125026,0.0033033856,0.0030920564,0.018502561,-0.07867415,0.04759748,-0.0029273403,0.071076624,-0.002380501,0.044347856,-0.113282934,0.014987032,0.038098942,0.047683362,0.0152156325,0.08433679,0.061223254,-0.014982735,0.01764294,0.0609843,0.014127814,0.041540287,0.030796645,0.010294839,0.018022208,0.07146625,0.007947411,-0.031477287,0.0475772,-0.04078935,-0.047865037,0.038517136,-0.0777393,0.0018817813,0.076303184,0.03219707,0.040794104,0.024777772,-0.019121371,-0.024525298,0.019179458,-0.023925155,-0.04425439,0.078839056,-0.01318064,0.039069436,-0.00448