e1f9732d-2397-4556-9c2c-acd0c3e7d1d9	45bef8c8-d1f0-4211-88da-52328f4acedd	0	## REST APIs vs. GraphQL\n\n| Feature | REST | GraphQL |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| **Endpoint structure** | Multiple, *resource‑centric* endpoints (e.g. `/users`, `/orders/123`) | Single, *query‑centric* endpoint (e.g. `/graphql`) |\n| **Data shape** | Fixed JSON payloads defined by the server | Flexible, client‑defined shape per query |\n| **HTTP usage** | Primarily `GET`, `POST`, `PUT`, `DELETE`, `PATCH` | Usually `POST` (or `GET` with query params) to the single endpoint |\n| **Versioning** | Often handled by URL versioning (`/v1/users`) | Schema evolution through deprecation and new fields |\n| **Caching** | Leveraged via HTTP headers (`ETag`, `Cache-Control`) | Requires client‑side or CDN caching strategies (e.g., persisted queries) |\n\n### Key Concepts Highlighted\n- **Endpoint**: REST exposes multiple URLs; GraphQL uses one URL with query payloads.\n- **Payload Flexibility**: REST delivers a fixed structure; GraphQL lets the client request exactly the fields it needs.\n	[0.025379604,0.056698333,-0.1528652,-0.023113871,0.10765689,-0.060116693,0.017514063,-0.034517962,-0.014996589,-0.040972278,0.00900878,0.002378281,0.05013555,-0.05425331,-0.008827226,-0.040024284,-0.0156491,-0.06842745,-0.018474339,0.048608612,-0.07086034,-0.006677343,0.009282342,-0.057130408,0.03774523,0.02609936,-0.031273067,0.009540785,-0.02933975,-0.0033697514,0.028769528,-0.00714568,-0.005849694,0.0028896441,-0.051295508,-0.011086549,0.015193837,0.0013232623,0.015999222,-0.013559487,0.04298549,0.0037781068,0.021604905,-0.052409917,0.010512926,-0.021118222,0.021266406,0.051537916,0.10625277,-0.10091894,-8.508032e-05,0.0323839,0.0008427486,-0.032137267,0.10249119,0.045228086,-0.027624931,0.05753919,-0.020147277,-0.035527162,0.07554787,0.06655301,-0.037186716,0.07038132,0.04847446,-0.026754165,-0.051381983,0.032031205,-0.008594423,-0.03914973,0.028808923,0.018718814,-0.0066951164,0.028983843,-0.016986616,-0.02