c1324e68-1ace-4366-b1bc-0828a8761066	45bef8c8-d1f0-4211-88da-52328f4acedd	1	- **Trade‑off**: *Simplicity* (REST’s clear, predictable routes) versus *Flexibility* (GraphQL’s granular data requests).\n\n### Illustrative Example\n\n```http\n# REST\nGET /users/42\n# Response\n{\n  "id": 42,\n  "name": "Alice",\n  "email": "alice@example.com",\n  "orders": [...]\n}\n```\n\n```graphql\n# GraphQL\nPOST /graphql\n{\n  "query": "\n    query GetUser($id: ID!) {\n      user(id: $id) {\n        id\n        name\n        email\n      }\n    }\n  ",\n  "variables": { "id": 42 }\n}\n# Response\n{\n  "data": {\n    "user": {\n      "id": 42,\n      "name": "Alice",\n      "email": "alice@example.com"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Broader Context\n\n- **Client‑Side Caching**: GraphQL benefits from libraries like Apollo Client, which automatically cache based on query shape. REST typically relies on HTTP caching or manual memoization.\n	[0.0021897112,0.08541434,-0.16989368,-0.04720526,0.079242885,-0.054386895,0.036697906,-0.0023213017,-0.03115062,-0.02658319,0.02148761,0.04094764,0.11052915,-0.010103594,-0.033676412,-0.01024906,-0.0019967959,-0.044481687,0.0022588165,0.046296485,-0.04406832,0.007204624,0.01747604,-0.066563465,0.045157272,0.0029813536,-0.03184229,-0.025288504,-0.029931873,0.040387526,0.018071132,-0.0036844378,-0.02828569,-0.028163416,-0.0989078,-0.007838626,0.0020588094,-0.012452229,0.03168819,0.026172478,0.07000989,0.053327348,0.020892939,-0.025313372,0.041010227,-0.00983899,0.034813866,0.020943798,0.11446131,-0.07235651,-0.02167327,-0.015512537,0.02155389,-0.02561731,0.060362313,0.052298993,0.009862589,0.059900276,-0.017540231,-0.06349602,0.08893615,0.028457046,-0.03747443,0.070565045,0.046181276,-0.019459967,-0.040610757,0.026425919,0.027670555,-0.03829698,0.045528643,0.015304767,-0.014887409,0.006273199,-0.017762749,-0.0058935904,-0.029236356,-0.05032568,0.019385565,0.04146243,-0.010533604,-0.021934623,0.031227296,-0.014554218,0.042121705,0.050640557,0.017315565,-0.0