d350a249-204a-41b4-ad16-264fa6c0757d	45bef8c8-d1f0-4211-88da-52328f4acedd	2	- **Rate Limiting & Throttling**: Both paradigms can expose per‑endpoint limits, but GraphQL can aggregate multiple resource requests into a single call, impacting how rate limits are applied.\n- **Evolution & Backwards Compatibility**: REST often introduces new endpoints for breaking changes, whereas GraphQL encourages *schema evolution* (adding fields, deprecating old ones) to maintain compatibility.\n- **Tooling & Ecosystem**: REST leverages tools like Swagger/OpenAPI for documentation; GraphQL uses the GraphQL schema itself as self‑documenting, supported by tools such as GraphQL Playground or GraphiQL.\n\n### Takeaway\n\nUnderstanding the *simplicity* of REST’s clear endpoint structure and the *flexibility* of GraphQL’s query‑based data shaping helps you decide which approach fits your use case—whether you prioritize straightforward integration or fine‑grained data retrieval.\n	[0.01630961,0.08442601,-0.15633446,-0.056188077,0.07214641,-0.06668419,0.046790138,0.02475534,0.004207188,-0.030363852,0.034169145,-0.027102403,0.08286986,-0.0020709068,0.015717408,-0.035373777,-0.03965521,-0.072282284,1.86119e-05,0.10500663,-0.05847638,-0.017352419,0.0015348556,-0.052706115,0.018936414,0.052680116,0.007764557,-0.013516976,-0.02180066,0.020252243,0.042321604,-0.04727766,0.0006971492,0.019593645,-0.06566793,-0.045470092,0.040501297,0.0011387418,0.009644344,0.004453146,0.067573085,-0.0039182794,0.01047232,-0.04075493,0.020272326,-0.021703435,0.06508362,-0.011822604,0.06974338,-0.10864063,0.018026741,-0.008585033,0.027886596,-0.0046773343,0.08880543,0.029416917,0.006313755,0.052572113,0.016859602,-0.086701535,0.055206195,0.046874225,-0.010787029,0.07191998,0.057122532,0.00037468883,-0.008413878,0.013646602,-0.036358755,-0.06446624,0.023024062,0.011148709,-0.034291007,0.023558099,-0.0097071035,0.024407612,-0.019921452,-0.03399161,-0.0173096,0.01907145,-0.027137868,-0.049695693,0.042942323,0.010541979,