d7f3d9f3-195a-4cdd-a145-84a0d8e9b9ee	f531310a-462c-4d49-ad8f-b42bfa0e41e1	0	# REST vs. GraphQL: A Quick Comparison  \n\n## Core Message  \n**REST** relies on *multiple endpoints* to expose resources, whereas **GraphQL** offers a *single flexible endpoint* that lets clients request exactly the data they need.\n\n---\n\n## Key Concepts\n\n| Concept | REST | GraphQL |\n|---------|------|---------|\n| **Endpoint structure** | One URL per resource (e.g., `/users/1`) | One URL (`/graphql`) for all queries |\n| **Data shape** | Fixed, defined by the server | Client‑defined via the query |\n| **Over‑/under‑fetching** | Common (fetch more than needed or need to call multiple endpoints) | Eliminated; client asks for exactly what it wants |\n| **Schema** | Implicit, inferred from responses | Explicit, type‑safe schema defined by the server |\n| **Query language** | HTTP verbs (`GET`, `POST`, `PUT`, `DELETE`) | GraphQL query language (query, mutation, subscription) |\n	[0.038744748,0.08008772,-0.1624632,-0.015195983,0.09030228,-0.058045506,0.013729677,-0.023360914,-0.020260539,-0.035614297,0.0250856,0.0061989427,0.042308923,-0.038393117,-0.008833921,-0.040411957,-0.014863105,-0.061934028,-0.021520237,0.06724635,-0.081686795,-0.014404743,0.009769544,-0.028887665,0.0541978,0.025547864,-0.020966815,0.022303602,-0.023908531,0.025796166,-0.0032299776,-0.0034592943,0.018386286,0.02836747,-0.07828498,-0.014263714,0.03126294,0.013778345,0.0042233425,-0.007733261,0.031253207,0.004043552,0.0042636176,-0.041742336,0.031866375,-0.040511332,0.031854432,0.0611592,0.08438069,-0.10643598,-0.024540935,0.011953459,-0.0112623265,-0.01771198,0.11087065,0.058817435,-0.0033330468,0.053844087,-0.00990415,-0.029991966,0.06900492,0.07590141,-0.04710694,0.08373969,0.0500509,-0.020047788,-0.04446841,0.016096206,-0.01190173,-0.03729579,0.027399866,0.01611316,0.015242455,0.019960538,-0.023077918,-0.019298172,-0.03550295,-0.032544672,0.000978919,0.015701601,-0.0064318357,-0.014063061,0.040173896,0.018779784