00d053a0-8b95-4306-83a0-973a34d35cc9	f531310a-462c-4d49-ad8f-b42bfa0e41e1	1	| **Versioning** | Usually via URL changes (`/v1/…`) | Usually not needed; schema evolution handled by deprecation |\n\n---\n\n## GraphQL’s One‑Endpoint Flexibility\n\n```graphql\n# GraphQL query example\n{\n  user(id: "123") {\n    id\n    name\n    posts(limit: 3) {\n      title\n      comments {\n        author { name }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n* **Single POST request** to `/graphql` carrying the query.\n* The response mirrors the shape of the query, avoiding unnecessary payload.\n* Clients can compose complex data structures in one round‑trip.\n\n---\n\n## Related Concepts (for Context)\n\n- **HTTP Methods** – REST’s CRUD operations are tied to verbs; GraphQL uses *queries* (read), *mutations* (write), and *subscriptions* (real‑time).\n- **Over‑fetching / Under‑fetching** – A pain point in REST that GraphQL directly addresses.\n- **Schema Introspection** – GraphQL servers expose a schema that clients can query (`__schema`) for type information.\n	[-0.0038796894,0.07769984,-0.15407866,-0.060066443,0.08258683,-0.101193115,0.013302077,0.04828087,-0.0067326333,-0.040407054,-0.021037534,0.025931055,0.0716002,-0.03904476,0.0010044096,-0.011494188,-0.027095087,-0.05739953,0.0030740716,0.038313355,-0.044340305,-0.0049218526,-0.031291783,-0.07604818,0.054522824,0.018395977,-0.0029981055,0.0011589244,-0.043308325,0.021331714,-0.016101798,0.021092933,-0.018428035,0.005200247,-0.04008798,-0.010375492,0.011449261,-0.0009152965,0.014816776,-0.014273879,0.0593527,-0.0019024465,-0.0017244763,-0.075357296,0.0070487657,-0.0044967984,0.079096474,-0.00010884443,0.09319959,-0.1122983,0.011984553,-0.016785258,0.057296712,-0.026548455,0.06658082,0.018096013,0.027063703,0.012922891,-0.021684324,-0.05322355,0.025142318,-0.0140736215,0.0017171082,0.06489433,0.028514221,-0.037007265,-0.033758614,0.036776286,0.01215508,-0.057195805,0.044842582,0.033102598,-0.010515281,0.070879936,0.010548389,0.019128753,-0.0