7af86da5-c6fa-4eaf-902b-81ca3796a1bf	f531310a-462c-4d49-ad8f-b42bfa0e41e1	2	- **Caching** – REST can leverage HTTP caching headers; GraphQL requires custom caching strategies (e.g., persisted queries, client‑side cache).\n- **Pagination** – REST often uses link headers; GraphQL can return cursor‑based pagination in a single response.\n\n---\n\n## Contextual Insights\n\n- **When to choose REST**  \n  * Simpler, well‑understood tooling.  \n  * Caching is straightforward with standard HTTP mechanisms.  \n  * When the data shape is stable and rarely changes.\n\n- **When GraphQL shines**  \n  * Mobile or bandwidth‑constrained clients need precise data.  \n  * Rapid UI iteration where data needs evolve frequently.  \n  * Complex relationships that would otherwise require many REST calls.\n\n- **Hybrid patterns** – Many production APIs expose both a REST layer for legacy consumers and a GraphQL layer for new ones, using the same underlying data sources.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n- **REST**: *Multiple, resource‑specific endpoints*; fixed payloads; straightforward caching.  \n	[-0.0048801894,0.08911891,-0.14268182,-0.061365154,0.06438334,-0.06851922,0.043204293,0.0048706187,-0.018821904,-0.04658791,-0.023186961,0.0030114525,0.06881285,-0.0037342408,0.029452465,-0.020559711,-0.003456039,-0.053434733,-0.009619283,0.075311355,-0.02764968,-0.026546853,0.07158002,-0.06365664,-0.0051141665,0.06642209,-0.0071312687,0.039935797,-0.03347607,0.022114497,0.06757698,-0.06928666,-0.026586393,-0.016984543,-0.041271638,-0.011071819,0.016815392,-0.03882128,0.03539496,0.040614475,0.05404572,0.005593555,0.01786589,-0.040581558,0.009048586,0.0067825536,0.00093546417,0.034746844,0.10055308,-0.0973706,0.011860841,0.012792916,0.02621613,-0.013683083,0.09978201,0.012805597,-0.0019032632,0.0699737,-0.0065436945,-0.07857588,0.07083338,0.045211542,-0.007626792,0.066424474,0.055459358,-0.043344267,-0.0147408545,0.0265616,-0.016986134,-0.020808237,0.045018554,-0.00064049347,-0.02336508,0.034342185,-0.005