86ab509d-82c1-4289-a6e1-32200220cb7d	4072e1b1-7f5f-4346-b7ea-b4f818cd61db	1	| `/evals/lib/resultComparator.ts` | Validates assertions against execution traces |\n| `/evals/lib/reportGenerator.ts` | Emits JSON/Markdown reports + radar charts |\n| `/evals/scenarios/` | YAML/JSON files describing test cases |\n| `/evals/fixtures/` | Static project templates used for fixtures |\n\n> **Key concept:** *Modular architecture* – each module has a single responsibility, enabling easy extension (new assertion types, new scoring dimensions, etc.).\n\n### 1.2 Evaluation Flow (Illustrated)\n\n```text\nUser → npx tsx evals/cli.ts --suite smoke\n   ↓\nParse CLI args (suite, tags, format)\n   ↓\nEvalRunner loads scenario list\n   ↓\nFor each scenario:\n  • Prepare fixture (tmp dir → template/git/empty)\n  • Execute scenario (agent/flow)\n  • Capture trace (tool calls, LLM calls, tokens)\n  • Validate against expectations\n  • Compute pass‑rate (assertions, semantic similarity, no errors)\n   ↓\nGenerate report (JSON + Markdown)\n   ↓\nPrint concise console summary\n```\n\n	[0.0162336,0.039581828,-0.16441976,-0.090277374,0.081588306,-0.06266575,-0.008241991,0.05803022,-0.052977666,-0.027462771,0.015204717,0.020878822,0.0825722,0.04858635,-0.04321738,-0.03841885,0.021014206,-0.0074162944,-0.02236084,0.004459678,0.04996144,-0.046438117,-0.024273837,-0.010385958,0.08538907,0.043183237,0.00524559,-0.006338824,-0.043860223,-0.033874407,0.052113496,-0.0017195585,-0.009311622,-0.045890246,-0.05823078,-0.0736809,0.02496878,0.0007964235,-0.03958792,-0.036448915,0.029756052,-0.024016995,-0.021813154,-0.023839593,0.031511027,-0.016534122,0.06954638,0.05312019,-0.004414123,-0.05604092,-0.024408057,0.023754748,0.05252221,-0.0031247872,0.10777799,0.024069378,-0.016021585,0.020708231,0.047136538,-0.05316202,0.047703918,0.04330104,-0.02880783,0.0622541,0.038662083,-0.028909544,-0.034899138,0.029611778,0.0068895086,-0.05706971,0.029106285,0.040271685,-0.035348523,-0.020841148,-0.016657755,0.008630208