60ebfff4-045f-4d95-8589-9dfc882cc234	4072e1b1-7f5f-4346-b7ea-b4f818cd61db	14	> **Professional insight:**  \n> Matric‑CLI’s evaluation framework exemplifies **best‑practice AI model assessment**: it combines *assertion‑level validation*, *rich execution tracing*, *multi‑dimensional scoring*, and *CI‑friendly reporting*.  \n> The design choices (voting, semantic similarity placeholder, exponential penalties, safety caps) mirror the strategies employed by top‑tier LLM evaluation suites (e.g., OpenAI’s `eval`, Anthropic’s `harness`).  \n> By structuring tests as **config‑driven YAML/JSON**, the system stays agnostic to the underlying LLM provider, making it straightforward to plug in new back‑ends (Ollama, OpenAI, even hybrid setups).\n\n---\n\n## 6. Integration Points\n\n| Integration | How it works |\n|-------------|--------------|\n| **CI/CD** | `npx tsx evals/cli.ts` emits JSON reports; CI can parse and fail on low pass‑rates. |\n| **GitHub** | Baseline commits are stored; regressions trigger GitHub issue creation. |\n	[0.0048842058,0.06726721,-0.15423387,-0.052750148,0.13015607,-0.043651007,0.04333314,0.057153884,-0.026143756,-0.050155595,0.007351017,0.017789362,0.04222759,-0.005009287,-0.014072383,-0.037448205,0.03928619,0.0054638665,-0.006090634,-0.0094995275,0.0014471881,-0.048820734,-0.044341244,-0.025525628,0.03729877,0.06023659,-0.057482447,0.013252304,-0.03291345,0.028381046,0.089240044,-0.05525721,-0.022762997,-0.0037045737,-0.092899345,9.713175e-05,0.016263187,0.05651051,-0.04315647,-0.015017188,-0.0019840582,0.033670478,0.00075068773,-0.04325543,0.050140608,-0.0059884186,0.07689287,0.028177705,0.040311333,-0.0779933,-0.03887265,0.014608389,0.025934538,0.05164876,0.056564942,0.02961095,-0.067774326,0.088622995,0.023634559,-0.082207516,0.012761576,0.02059934,-0.053022403,0.01242387,0.009360672,-0.0043592975,-0.014961907,0.0444722,0.03410381,-0.027115459,0.041839797,0.020734662,-0.037003383,0.0041216565,-0.033820502,0.0417611,-0.017824497,-0.08088173,-0.0432