c13d9b04-f554-445b-ab0b-59519482c343	95cdbc99-53f9-4de8-8f88-220e9508ab17	0	# Feature Idea: Temporal Note Decay\n\n**Concept** – Give each note a *half‑life* so that its relevance naturally declines over time, unless it is actively revisited or referenced.  \n\nThe decay mechanism is **reversible**: any access (open, edit, link‑to) resets the timer.  \nThis mirrors human forgetting and keeps search results fresh without permanently deleting data.\n\n---\n\n## The Concept in Detail\n\n| Element | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| **Decay Trigger** | Number of days since last access. |\n| **Decay Function** | Exponential, analogous to radioactive decay. |\n| **Reinforcement** | Accessing a note multiplies the relevance score back to its base value. |\n| **Backlink Weight** | Notes with more backlinks decay *slower*, preserving core knowledge. |\n\n**Formula**\n\n```sql\nrelevance_score = base_score * exp(-λ * days_since_access)\n```\n\n- `λ` (lambda) is the decay constant controlling the half‑life.  \n	[0.06668537,0.047100272,-0.18368247,-0.0766918,0.09239573,-0.04342688,0.03536354,0.031976495,0.044145033,-0.06400144,-0.03895195,0.057727817,0.07016187,0.030871745,0.029829374,-0.025801701,0.037623845,-0.05777322,-0.009012156,0.041602563,-0.0039337967,-0.034020796,-0.04382057,-0.06421361,0.032479875,0.0640723,-0.0073413365,0.0073262197,-0.024896907,0.05197859,0.055368613,-0.027868167,-0.039163947,-0.0071294266,-0.041816767,-0.050856106,0.041490484,0.032181036,0.009624552,0.010886478,0.028471975,0.044656113,0.032280143,0.0075405673,0.06358264,0.0021822935,0.027057063,0.020254273,0.07183574,-0.08332875,0.0040058596,0.030582486,0.038766053,0.010594464,0.057992347,0.027541699,-0.005200676,-0.0032277994,0.015347995,-0.015579368,0.09654248,0.017104745,-0.0147051085,0.10011802,0.045631416,-0.03725511,-0.014807094,0.031821795,0.014486321,-0.052618265,0.038632527,0.019838866,-0.05049173,0.03829582,-0.00062704756,0.014179766,-0.03045722,-0.022366507,0.0015317727,0.02577