aecf6f4d-6a4b-461a-9852-ec81907d8e75	1c77dc3b-b229-4bb8-97e2-c2d90385e4a0	3	| **Backlink weighting (`α`)** | Set between 0.05–0.2; too high and old knowledge never fades. |\n| **Recalculation frequency** | Incremental updates on access events; batch recomputation nightly for long‑tail decay. |\n| **User controls** | Allow users to pin notes (lock decay) or manually adjust decay rates. |\n| **Monitoring** | Track search relevance scores, click‑through rates, and retrieval latency to validate the model. |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Broader Implications\n\n- **Human memory models**: The decay approach aligns with ACT‑R and other cognitive architectures that simulate forgetting and relearning.  \n- **Knowledge management best practices**: Periodic review cycles are often recommended; automated decay provides a lightweight, continuous alternative.  \n- **AI‑assisted curation**: Combined with Matric’s semantic search, the system can surface forgotten yet valuable insights at just the right moment.\n\n---\n\n### Key Takeaways\n\n	[0.062308088,0.008612078,-0.16048595,-0.06409298,0.09371344,-0.03763533,0.062262774,0.008945857,0.01668707,-0.021930758,-0.010649867,0.024814062,0.09552113,0.06416142,0.02144924,-0.029906603,0.035938583,-0.041062936,0.004814605,0.04638466,0.03009251,-0.014458993,-0.022512043,-0.023537565,-0.0062530064,0.10932649,-0.041094806,0.01632333,-0.018250147,0.04126672,0.08849896,-0.0588393,-0.05833933,-0.0128687695,-0.054942794,-0.047713358,0.084316984,0.013147696,0.013940714,-0.0016178086,0.05832283,0.034147408,0.06645967,-0.01656122,0.046465345,0.033369787,0.03896377,-0.036718886,0.05241683,-0.06615362,0.023149727,-0.0054286807,0.016924683,0.001773431,0.054846313,0.026112983,-0.022012725,0.007546751,-0.019278811,-0.036194,0.08320808,0.027217235,-0.023823153,0.06424118,0.029250598,0.008827398,-0.028170204,0.030000309,0.013263051,-0.063217215,0.04192894,-0.009062684,-0.04557665,0.01923512,-0.017298685,0.0034063233,-0.018062253,-0.058705382,0.019523913,0.02816515,-0.0