e4652e71-0a7c-41bb-9b86-f22a23152ac8	26d57c87-5712-47fb-95fc-80b61c04f061	0	# Feature Idea: The Blind Spot Detector\n\n---\n\n## 1. Problem Statement  \nWe often *don’t know what we don’t know*.  \nIn a growing knowledge base, invisible gaps can remain unnoticed, leaving us with an incomplete view of our own expertise.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Proposed Solution – Anti‑Search  \n\n### Core Idea  \nInstead of searching for *what exists*, the system searches for *what should exist but doesn’t*.\n\n### How it Works  \n\n| Step | Description | Technical Hint |\n|------|-------------|----------------|\n| 1 | **Semantic Space Analysis** – Embed every note (e.g., using sentence‑transformers) into a high‑dimensional vector space. | `sentence-transformers` + cosine similarity |\n| 2 | **Hole Detection** – Identify sparsely populated clusters where note density falls below a threshold. | `hdbscan` or `DBSCAN` on embeddings |\n	[0.015490249,0.06313034,-0.19950911,-0.049417384,0.10584326,0.023336358,0.036075056,0.0031201537,-0.03365332,-0.057099197,-0.016289419,0.036526397,0.059536677,0.04473313,-0.021995062,-0.0054050335,0.0041088588,-0.042062648,-0.023003329,0.055836573,-0.035060115,0.01465257,0.032503594,-0.0132230995,0.04322062,0.07141151,-0.012058402,-0.02229362,0.018317666,-0.027627984,0.066138014,-0.031266857,-0.019551048,-0.023711603,-0.07689524,-0.01738366,0.048247486,0.036612976,-0.0027296946,0.03046382,0.034512475,0.01857499,0.00037518106,-0.07160233,0.040749285,0.007065673,0.025767047,0.0044956882,0.06913028,-0.09065284,0.009988525,-0.00075260055,0.056862798,0.01117705,0.04606449,0.0378697,0.020501228,-0.033283684,0.06407161,-0.04246554,0.06366414,0.058047503,-0.038731772,0.08972316,0.009821544,-0.009771438,-0.033431526,0.054329306,0.009583666,-0.068937674,0.047683377,-0.004233296,0.016282115,0.03062919,-0.062351443,0.00047498386,-0.017564878,0.03524746,0.01239987,0.050915867,0.0035711047,0.0068810144,0.07668134,0.012076224,0.08481903,0.0015773668,-0.020865658,-0.025011307,-0