49b1fce3-77be-446b-a933-4c91e014db93	26d57c87-5712-47fb-95fc-80b61c04f061	2	- **Gap → Idea** – “Your notes lack a section on X → Consider a new project or paper.”  \n- **Idea ↔ Knowledge** – Prompt users to explore under‑connected topics.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Wild Extension – Auto‑Research\n\nWhen a gap is flagged, offer an *Auto‑Research* prompt:\n\n> “I noticed you have no notes on **[Topic]**. Would you like me to fetch a primer from the web and create a starter note?”\n\nThis reduces friction in knowledge expansion and keeps the repository self‑updating.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Related Concepts (Knowledge Base)\n\n| Feature | Relevance to Blind Spot Detector |\n|---------|----------------------------------|\n| **Temporal Note Decay** | Combining decay with gap detection can surface *forgotten* or *outdated* topics that should be revisited. |\n| **Note DNA** | Embedding the *origin* and *purpose* of each note helps refine the reference ontology and improves gap identification accuracy. |\n	[0.027802711,0.03315545,-0.16191943,-0.08352165,0.09219641,0.0031837136,0.052905243,-0.0018280015,0.020932019,-0.074610315,0.0014303315,0.019620445,0.036044,0.07191597,0.01772287,-0.051181987,0.022065159,-0.05917804,0.008873184,0.03711717,0.012578855,0.012556265,-0.030034391,-0.05655684,0.024260022,0.043683965,-0.012281893,-0.025243068,-0.045683257,0.03188989,0.05887321,-0.044594146,-0.006236943,0.008704328,-0.05414264,-0.029947681,0.045874763,-0.007847051,-0.040983677,-0.00012500063,0.07340017,0.047548167,-0.021345187,-0.024002902,0.01820991,-0.002057151,0.016789626,-0.009379015,0.08083983,-0.082265384,0.03926928,0.0767682,0.046182394,0.019353254,0.056313407,0.05397617,-0.022887308,-0.030870238,0.07126004,-0.03604772,0.040825024,0.061405197,-0.0073211966,0.09728105,-0.009788358,-0.013788029,-0.041688275,0.04278055,-0.0042011323,-0.086561725,0.026472734,0.038916364,-0.036411002,0.06744398,-0.056331795,0.029401254,-0.013028277,-0.006083773,0.0147109935,-0.0035281975,0.014067815,0.010623825,0