f009c5a2-7329-472f-be29-548648c2d2a4	e4cb1d19-6a3b-462f-a4a9-3f9c309047d3	1	- **Growth** – The accelerating user base and feature set of the Matric platform necessitates careful consideration of how bulk operations (like the one used to create *Test Bulk 1*) are handled in both RESTful and GraphQL architectures.  \n\n---\n\n### Contextual Insights  \n\n- **Bulk Endpoint Design** – When creating resources en masse, REST typically requires multiple calls to distinct endpoints (e.g., `/tests`, `/tests/1`, `/tests/2`…), whereas GraphQL can bundle these creations into a single mutation request.  \n- **Scalability** – Rapid platform growth increases the load on bulk endpoints. Choosing an architecture that minimizes round‑trips (GraphQL) or optimizes batch processing (REST) can help maintain performance.  \n- **Data Consistency** – With multiple endpoints, REST may expose intermediate states that need to be reconciled, whereas GraphQL can return the final state in a single response, reducing the risk of stale data during bulk operations.  \n\n---\n	[-0.012724835,0.09645571,-0.16211055,-0.025940174,0.114117004,-0.083107315,0.055747744,0.009703115,-0.014451753,-0.075209185,0.025116615,0.011174218,0.050636344,0.024077155,-0.028022218,-0.04023881,0.023678117,-0.06821738,-0.002435346,0.07767102,-0.00043834792,-0.024811264,0.016426751,-0.044432655,0.055920966,0.07538927,-0.013990961,0.029885115,-0.017679043,0.008204933,0.046377297,-0.043432172,0.013621017,0.04543931,-0.06730496,-0.04147797,0.029382192,-0.02913372,-0.0013281408,-0.02856199,0.025326965,-0.012275024,0.000387087,-0.054636616,0.026223222,0.0071094087,0.07173484,0.0031824575,0.07775656,-0.08731713,0.009475734,0.023855658,-0.011616655,-0.0077124704,0.06735297,0.044042207,-0.053601146,0.058206435,-0.005890223,-0.033770185,0.037347175,0.028173057,-0.01922586,0.07833664,0.043778352,-0.018281579,-0.0049389256,0.0033526248,0.009080466,-0.03971225,0.035472665,0.017159618,-0.024978217,0.011503332,0.025369287,-0.009856007,-0.