750d88ee-6ac5-4f53-b4af-4b5d4bc3ba67	81b961d9-8881-483d-b7e6-e365bef92154	0	# Test Bulk 2  \n\nTest **Bulk 2** was created through the **bulk endpoint**.  \nThis illustrates how a single API call can submit many records at once, a common pattern for batch processing in both REST and GraphQL services.\n\n---\n\n## Related Concept\n\n### REST vs. GraphQL – Endpoint Design  \n\n> **REST** uses multiple endpoints, each exposing a fixed data structure.  \n> **GraphQL** exposes a single flexible endpoint that lets the client request exactly the fields it needs.\n\nThis difference influences how bulk operations are implemented:  \n- In **REST**, a dedicated `/bulk` endpoint is often provided.  \n- In **GraphQL**, the client can send a single mutation that contains multiple items or use query batching.\n\n---\n\n## Key Concepts\n\n| Concept | Notes |\n|---------|-------|\n| **REST vs. GraphQL** | Exploring differences in endpoint structure, data shape, and query flexibility. |\n	[0.0076156086,0.05107526,-0.1741444,-0.029948276,0.074948244,-0.07293573,0.02767396,-0.005927556,-0.05436515,-0.04836393,-0.009227335,0.014536679,0.086859494,-0.026869096,-0.011806829,-0.062370323,0.01767718,-0.094480895,-0.007961733,0.07131614,-0.017153366,0.008853281,0.015864886,-0.038517464,0.04032635,0.04933775,0.0021061131,-0.0025016677,-0.036647398,-0.0129598575,0.033304825,-0.0051780446,0.02549958,0.008766642,-0.08356986,-0.034144502,0.022117678,-0.02557477,0.009015379,-0.00090753596,0.040577635,0.01059449,0.010550923,-0.052520894,-0.021592993,-0.024021223,0.037663035,0.038356885,0.06271527,-0.09916605,-0.00070558896,-0.014860177,-0.038136546,-0.008376312,0.054351658,0.05203933,-0.034195296,0.07361918,0.016880285,-0.02200777,0.056938592,0.043183878,-0.026095621,0.10026018,0.0502037,-0.018080743,-0.022435507,0.0037709817,0.013329656,-0.062687814,0.023478428,0.0068463525,-0.0054171565,-0.013143734,0.024428021,0.0030349428,-0.029490087,-0.02790481,-0.005855438,0.027277585,-0.017291889,-0.0428069