699f5997-747e-4c88-aacd-f89556336f11	81b961d9-8881-483d-b7e6-e365bef92154	2	  - Better memory efficiency for certain workloads.  \n  - Extended Lua scripting support.  \n\nWhen designing a bulk endpoint, consider how caching will be applied:  \n- **REST**: Cache whole responses per endpoint.  \n- **GraphQL**: Cache at the field or query level, potentially leveraging a GraphQL‑specific cache layer.\n\n---\n\n## Contextual Insight\n\nBulk endpoints are essential when ingesting large datasets, such as bulk tests, orders, or logs.  \nChoosing the right API design (REST vs. GraphQL) and a capable caching layer (Valkey vs. Redis) can dramatically affect performance, developer experience, and system scalability.  \n\nBy understanding the trade‑offs in endpoint structure and caching strategy, you can build a more efficient and maintainable API surface.\n	[0.006304208,0.12563498,-0.13156457,-0.037936397,0.07500688,-0.067829214,0.0746896,-0.0012360498,-0.023397893,-0.0016366093,0.0044394396,0.0021919291,0.067289054,0.0016760643,-0.00870903,-0.010438125,0.025296759,-0.052510023,0.019105883,0.0444432,-0.027880765,-0.03704049,0.01741419,-0.041045874,0.019679978,0.06897022,-0.028618747,0.03294524,-0.003518124,0.014267972,0.05448927,-0.045833036,-0.042419568,0.007693291,-0.054829773,-0.033067677,-0.012591184,-0.002087697,-0.0040085507,-0.023644814,0.04166886,0.011640395,0.022830961,-0.055392325,0.021541614,-0.014172994,-0.017014384,-0.002892473,0.09675712,-0.10561135,0.013696421,-0.031249251,-0.0096012615,-0.0069094137,0.052104913,0.017850447,-0.0382895,0.063126035,0.00068606855,-0.066700965,0.07753848,0.041060247,-0.08396957,0.09136969,0.045057014,-0.0192173,-0.019175483,-0.012602358,0.0039158957,-0.05021942,0.033277266,-0.0012680358,-0.029352378,-0.005972204,-0.03097467,-0.011124861,-0.047124498,-0.011883447,-0.0029785044,0.03642654,-0.011033142,-0.059044372,0.047576956,-0.0062049055,0.039189354,0.004603072,-0.045604628,-0.024404323,-0.028913407,0.10862249,-0.043435246,0.0017424