6e955376-1bc2-4016-ab27-1c2952a3b5da	6da54f64-fc02-4915-99b3-9a5cf483eb3f	# MCP Memory Module Test\n\nTesting the matric-memory module for Claude Code integration.\n\n## Features to Verify\n- Note creation with markdown\n- Semantic search capabilities\n- Tag management\n- Link detection between notes\n\n## Related Concepts\nThis relates to [[Meeting Notes]] for API integration work.\n\n```bash\n# Test code block handling\necho "Does it preserve formatting?"\n```	sha256:7554c522784186518d1e0b26b67d386b9ac24faaa924a8d07a0e9eca0056c9bd	2026-01-05 02:54:40.503595-05	\N	\N
cb4d38f8-1eeb-4984-b5cc-51fde0dd0a25	661216f0-b9d3-493d-b0cb-b96b6a3e8089	# MCP Server Test Note\n\nTesting write capability from Claude Code session.\n\n## Timestamp\n2026-01-05 ~08:00 EST\n\n## Verdict\n- Gitea: Working\n- Hound: Working (but sysops not indexed)\n- Memory: Testing now...	sha256:117b93f2126901e6064443b0847226021978d7d0df4310d020860bcd0a1be462	2026-01-05 12:09:48.050583-05	\N	\N
4829ca10-fab2-46df-827b-71ff96947fa8	0aa61cf4-e0b6-4b12-8e50-57055fc72ed5	# Architecture Decision: VM Overlay Strategy\n\n## Context\nNeed to decide between thick provisioning vs COW overlays for role-based VMs on titan/grissom.\n\n## Options Considered\n1. **Full clones** - Independent, large, slow to create\n2. **COW overlays** - Shared base, small delta, instant creation\n3. **Linked clones** - Middle ground, libvirt native\n\n## Decision\nCOW overlays with frozen base image. Rationale:\n- 40GB base shared across 4 VMs = 120GB savings\n- Instant VM creation for testing\n- Clear trust boundary (overlay = dirty, base = clean)\n\n## Consequences\n- Must maintain base image compatibility\n- Cannot update base without rebuilding overlays\n- Snapshot chains can get deep	sha256:cbca6484e503bc68fb2e75e630f0fa57f84cfc6f0cf4941e65ff9b263ae79e99	2026-01-05 12:42:54.017845-05	\N	\N
3031ec31-c2e0-47eb-842e-6b2fea1e7d83	f9844d30-23ba-4264-b957-a66a41e6b503	Quick note: grissom bluetooth audio cuts out when switching between headphones and speakers. Seems related to PipeWire not releasing the old sink fast enough. Workaround is to restart wireplumber.\n\nAlso the RTX 3060 runs hot (82C) under sustained load - might need to repaste.	sha256:aa083a50f8d72537b9afb772cc7032be8610c3e3fcd89b67da36dd05e4eb2928	2026-01-05 12:42:54.147411-05	\N	\N
be31bb88-a017-4ac2-83e7-bc1f86af09ac	2ab2af54-26b2-4ab0-a02f-5e04a3377b3c	# PipeWire vs PulseAudio Migration Notes\n\nMigrated titan and grissom from PulseAudio to PipeWire.\n\n## What worked\n- Drop-in replacement, most apps just work\n- Lower latency for pro audio\n- Better Bluetooth codec support (LDAC, aptX)\n\n## What broke\n- OBS audio monitoring required manual sink config  \n- Some Electron apps (Discord) needed restart\n- pavucontrol shows weird sink names\n\n## Key commands\n```bash\n# Check PipeWire status\nsystemctl --user status pipewire pipewire-pulse wireplumber\n\n# List sinks\npactl list sinks short\n\n# Force codec for BT device\npactl send-message /card/bluez_card.XX_XX_XX set-profile a2dp-sink-ldac\n```	sha256:5fa56b9a281f55def2126b367d17a29fd9898cb022d617f8c7a72014eb066efc	2026-01-05 12:42:54.296734-05	\N	\N
