75164833-70f9-47e9-8948-734d1f00cbf9	0aa61cf4-e0b6-4b12-8e50-57055fc72ed5	# Architecture Decision: VM Overlay Strategy\n\n## Context\nWe must choose between thick provisioning and copy‑on‑write (COW) overlays for role‑based VMs on the **titan** and **grissom** clusters.\n\n## Options Considered\n1. **Full clones** – Completely independent images; large disk usage and slow creation.  \n2. **COW overlays** – Share a read‑only base image, storing only the dirty pages; small delta files and near‑instant VM creation.  \n3. **Linked clones** – An intermediate approach that is native to libvirt.\n\n## Decision\n**Use COW overlays with a frozen base image.**  \n\nRationale:\n- A 40 GB base image can be shared by four VMs, yielding a 120 GB storage saving.  \n- VMs can be spawned instantly for testing and development.  \n- The overlay represents the “dirty” state, while the base remains clean, providing a clear trust boundary.\n\n## Consequences\n- The base image must remain compatible with all overlays.  \n- Updating the base image requires rebuilding or re‑cloning all dependent overlays.  \n- Snapshot chains may become deep, which can impact performance if not managed.	AI-enhanced revision	2026-01-12 09:13:08.925337-05	\N	\N
7220ef7e-3798-4115-84ff-0b997dd60b76	f9844d30-23ba-4264-b957-a66a41e6b503	# Quick Note\n\n- **Bluetooth audio issue**  \n  The Grissom device cuts out when switching between headphones and speakers. It seems PipeWire isn’t releasing the old sink quickly enough.  \n  **Workaround:** restart WirePlumber.  \n  ```bash\n  systemctl restart wireplumber\n  ```\n\n- **GPU temperature**  \n  The RTX 3060 reaches about 82 °C under sustained load. This may warrant repasting to improve cooling.	AI-enhanced revision	2026-01-12 09:13:11.748991-05	\N	\N
