f3779c2d-addd-4d77-b43d-bd612deaf331	2ab2af54-26b2-4ab0-a02f-5e04a3377b3c	---\n# PipeWire vs PulseAudio Migration Notes\n\nMigrated **titan** and **grissom** from PulseAudio to PipeWire.\n\n## What Worked\n\n- **Drop‑in replacement** – most applications continue to function without modification.\n- **Lower latency** – ideal for professional audio workflows.\n- **Improved Bluetooth codecs** – native support for LDAC and aptX.\n\n## What Broke\n\n- **OBS audio monitoring** – requires manual sink configuration to route monitoring correctly.\n- **Electron applications** (e.g., Discord) – need to be restarted after the switch.\n- **pavucontrol** – displays odd sink names (e.g., `bluez_card.XX_XX_XX`) that can be confusing.\n\n## Key Commands\n\n```bash\n# Verify PipeWire and related services are running\nsystemctl --user status pipewire pipewire-pulse wireplumber\n\n# List all available sinks\npactl list sinks short\n\n# Force a Bluetooth device to use the LDAC codec\npactl send-message /card/bluez_card.XX_XX_XX set-profile a2dp-sink-ldac\n```\n\n---	AI-enhanced revision	2026-01-12 09:13:14.53574-05	\N	\N
